summary: A fire alarm malfunction at the Eiffel Tower prompted the evacuation of approximately 1,200 tourists. Despite initial reports of a fire, the cause was later identified as a malfunction in the alarm system. No injuries were reported, and the situation was resolved swiftly. The Eiffel Tower was temporarily closed while authorities investigated the incident, but it is expected to reopen soon.

name: Home Alone
summary: The enduring classic "Home Alone" has sparked renewed interest with a resurgence of news articles exploring its enduring legacy. One article delves into the behind-the-scenes revelation of a "horrific" line that a cast member struggled to deliver to Macaulay Culkin. Another piece features an interview with Culkin himself, where he recounts his experience making the film. The versatility of the film is highlighted by an article explaining an unscripted mishap between Culkin and Joe Pesci. House Beautiful showcases the iconic home featured in the movie, revealing fascinating details and trivia. The Daily Mail provides a comprehensive list of lesser-known facts about "Home Alone." A humorous CinemaBlend article examines the inconsistencies and absurdities found in "Home Alone 2," while the Express reveals the surprising age of one of the Wet Bandits. LADbible teases the upcoming "Home Alone 3" sequel, set in 2025 and featuring the return of the Wet Bandits. Additionally, UNILAD highlights Macaulay Culkin's shrewd contract negotiation that netted him an additional $18 million, and Digital Spy announces the timely televised airing of "Home Alone" during the Christmas season.
